## Why accessibility IDs cause retries and timeouts

Each token test follows this chain (updated flow):

```
navigateToWidget()
  → [home-page widgets] stay on Main — no nav link tap
  → [other widgets] ensure home → swipe until ~{widget}_link_caption → tap
  → wait widget-specific page-ready sentinel (from widget-xpaths, not ~exinput_i)
getCachedStylesObject()
  → wait for style input (~exinput_i or ~exinput1_i for modal/bottomsheet)
  → read ~label2_caption
  → on failure: recoverWidgetContext() → back-to-home → re-navigate
  → session dies → MobileSessionGuard marks dead → later tokens fail fast
```

**One missing or slow accessibility ID → 30s wait × 3 retries × recovery loops → minutes per widget.**

Fix the IDs first. Timeout/retry tuning only helps after elements are findable within a few seconds.

