## Selector layers (configured in `MobileSelectors.ts`)

| Layer | Accessibility ID | Used for |
|-------|------------------|----------|
| Home header | `~mobile_navbar1_title` | Confirm app is on Main/home |
| Back button | `~mobile_navbar1_backbtn_icon` | Return to home during recovery |
| Nav link | `~{widget}_link_caption` | Tap widget on home scroll list (**not used for tabbar/navbar**) |
| Page header | Widget-specific (see `headers` + `widget-xpaths.ts`) | Confirm widget page loaded |
| Style console input | `~exinput_i` (default) | Type RN style commands |
| Style console input (special) | `~exinput1_i` | bottomsheet, modal-dialog |
| Style output | `~label2_caption` | Read JSON result |
| Form-wrapper header | `~entestkey_i` | form-wrapper page header only |
| Login header | `loggedInUserForm1_submit_formAction_a` | login page header (no `~` prefix) |

**Home-page page-ready sentinels:**

| Widget | Page ready ID | Nav link used? |
|--------|---------------|----------------|
| tabbar | `~mobile_tabbar1` | No — verify on Main |
| navbar | `~mobile_navbar1_title` | No — verify on Main |
| modal-dialog | `~dialog1_icon_caption` | Yes — `~modaldialog_link_caption` |

**Known design issue (remaining):** Many widgets still use `~exinput_i` as page header in `MobileSelectors.headers` until Inspector IDs are filled in. Code prefers widget-specific sentinels from `widget-xpaths.ts` when header is still `~exinput_i`.

**Build #74 nav/home failures during recovery:** Partially addressed by back-to-home + swipe-until-visible. Tabbar/navbar nav failures (51× / 58×) were largely **wrong flow** (tapping nav link for a widget already on Main).

