## Recommended fix order

Work top-down. Verify each ID on a real BrowserStack session (Appium Inspector or `browser.$('~id').isDisplayed()`).

### Sprint 1 — iOS style console (fixes ~370 broken tests)

1. ~~tabbar, navbar~~ → **home-page flow + Main style console verified** (`~exinput_i` / `~label2_caption`)  
2. chips, checkboxset, panel, radioset  
3. datetime, message, cards, button, checkbox, toggle  
4. bottomsheet (`~exinput1_i` input + fix page-ready header — should not use `~exinput_i`)

**For each widget:** Open widget page on iOS → confirm style input + `~label2_caption`. Update `MobileSelectors.ts` / `widget-xpaths.ts` if IDs differ.

### Sprint 2 — Android nav + special inputs (fixes ~100 broken tests)

1. ~~modal-dialog~~ → **IDs verified**; re-run spec to confirm nav 82× resolved  
2. ~~tabs~~ → **All IDs verified** (`~tabs1_headers_0_title` page ready)  
3. progress-bar, progress-circle, picture, button  

### Sprint 3 — Shared / suspicious IDs

1. ~~accordion-pane~~ → **same as accordion** (shared nav verified)  
2. ~~panel-footer~~ → **same as panel** (shared nav verified)  
3. form-wrapper header `~entestkey_i` vs style input `~exinput_i`  
4. login header `loggedInUserForm1_submit_formAction_a`

### Sprint 4 — Navigation flow ✅ DONE (in code)

- ✅ Back-to-home before tapping nav link during recovery  
- ✅ Widget-specific page-ready sentinel (via `getPageHeaderSelector` + `widget-xpaths.ts`)  
- ✅ Skip navigation when already on target widget / home-page widget  
- ✅ Swipe until nav link visible (`swipeUntilElementVisible`)  
- ✅ Home-page widgets: tabbar + navbar (`HOME_PAGE_WIDGETS`)  
- ✅ Dead session fast-fail (`mobileSessionGuard.ts`) — partial; spec-level skip still optional

